<h1>@HI{{kurai}}/@HI{{gurai}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <em>number/counter</em> <strong>@HI{{kurai}}</strong>
<li> <em>demonstrative</em> <strong>@HI{{kurai}}</strong>
<li> <em>interrogative pronoun</em> <strong>@HI{{kurai}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{kurai}}</strong> indicates an approximate amount without saying anything about the amount's
upper or lower limits.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kokokarasono@KJ{{study^mingle}}made@KJ{{car}}de30@KJ{{part}}<strong>kurai</strong>kakarimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      From here it takes about 30 minutes to get to that school by car.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<hr>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{kurai}}</strong> is used to indicate the extent of an action.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{shame}}zukashikute@KJ{{hole}}gaattara@KJ{{enter}}ritai<strong>kurai</strong>datta.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I was so embarrassed that I felt like crawling into a hole.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<hr>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{kurai}}</strong> is used to indicate a comparison.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{mountain^lower}}sannno@KJ{{new}}shii@KJ{{house}}no@KJ{{courtyard}},@KT{{gorufu}}@KJ{{location}}
      <strong>gurai</strong>no@KJ{{large}}kisada.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The garden at Yamashita's new house is as big as a golf course.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<hr>
</p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
There is no difference in meaning between <strong>@HI{{kurai}}</strong> and <strong>@HI{{gurai}}</strong>.
</p>

